<normalizedToken id="18BAAB8E7847D4B4DA1F162386A8061A" originalValue="LeÃ³n">Leon</normalizedToken>
), in oak forests on limestone soils in the mountains in the vicinity of Cerro El Viejo, 1200-1500 m in elevation (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="C71C328A9A5E0872B13D8213EEAB7114" captionStart="Figure 51" captionStartId="F51" captionText="Figure 51. Map of geographic distribution of L. hintonii based on herbarium specimen data." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.168.51904.figure51" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/480063" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">51</figureCitation>
